+Issue : - OGW is not able to identify the relevant OrderLine for which the device has been handed out to customer in VORAS shop part of ShiptoStore scenario .+

 

2 possible flavors here ,
 # Order have single Orderline applicable for eSIMPush.
 # Order have more than one order lines applicable for eSIMPush .

 

+Scenario -1 : -+ 

Should and can be handled by OGW directly as part of this defect .

 

While receiving SetOrderStatus from VORAS VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT , loop over the entire order to identify the OrderLine having eSIMPush

/CDM/Customer/Subscriber/Target/Attributes/Attribute[Code=ESIMPush] = 'YES'

 

IF,

We don’t have any such OrderLine.

              Then, Do nothing.

Else,

If ,

We have more than one

Then, Do nothing.

Else,

Use the OrderLine to use further for eSIMPush Process.

 

+Scenario -2 : -+ 

 

Will be handled as part of DF -Phase3 epic.

 

Probable solutions hint:

              +Solution- 1:+
 # Omnius will send the OrderLine(s) towards SAP and then SAP will send it subsequently towards VORAS.
 # VORAS will forward OrderLineID over SetOrderStatus call to connect between exact order line.
 ## We will also need to remove the code we are building part of solution 1.

 

+Solution- 2:+
 # Voras will call GetOrder to connect between OrderLineID and the device ID.
 # VORAS will forward the OrderLineID over SetOrderStatus call to connect between exact order line.
 ## We will also need to remove the code we are building part of solution 1.;;;

03/Jul/24 11:49 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Irina added  a comment -
 
 
Hi [~pallavi.chaudhari1@vodafone.com] ,
In ProcessOrderRequest SALES_PHASE provided for <dlc:SkuID>R623.5000000523-24,FTTH-L2-BSA</dlc:SkuID>. But we do not have such SkuID in the ProcessOrderRequest in <dlc:CommercialProduct>. That`s why we do not send it to OGW.

!image-2024-07-03-15-18-48-383.png!

When we create the Request to OGW: for each CommercialProduct (from ProcessOrderRequest) we`re looking for the appropriate SkuID in the Component and  if we have SALES_PHASE\rollout_status etc  we create them under OGW CommercialList as SystemAdditionalData.

In SIT1 example we have a list of  SkuID  as one SkuID
<dlc:SkuID>R623.5000000524-24,FTTH-L2-BSA</dlc:SkuID>
I think these values should be splitted.
We`ve already had such kind of issue and it was resolved by providing the new pcat by Marco.;;;

if we are going to change it, it would be a multimapper fix.

I’ll discuss it internally if we should fix it or not (as this parameter was already in previous phase).;;;
